 href="/w/opensearch_desc.php" title="Wikipedia (en)"/> <link rel="EditURI" type="application/rsd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/> <link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/> <link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gag"/> <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/> <link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" /> <!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/w/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1"></script><![endif]--> </head> <body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Gag rootpage-Gag skin-vector action-view">		<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div> 		<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div> 		<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main"> 			<a id="top"></a> 			<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div><div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content"> </div> <h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Gag</h1>			<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content"> 				<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>				<div id="contentSub"></div> 								<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump"> 					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a> 				</div> 				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Gag_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Gag (disambiguation)">Gag (disambiguation)</a>.</div> <table class="plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Refimprove" role="presentation"> <tr> <td class="mbox-image"> <div style="width:52px"><a href="/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png" width="50" height="39" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="399" /></a></div> </td> <td class="mbox-text"> <div class="mbox-text-span">This article <b>needs additional citations for <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability">verification</a></b>. <span class="hide-when-compact">Please help <a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit">improve this article</a> by <a href="/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1" title="Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.</span> <small><i>(January 2014)</i></small> <small class="hide-when-compact"><i>(<a href="/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" title="Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div> </td> </tr> </table> <div class="thumb tright"> <div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg/220px-Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg" width="220" height="147" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg/330px-Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg/440px-Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2592" data-file-height="1728" /></a> <div class="thumbcaption"> <div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Ferrachu._Ball_gag.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div> a woman wearing a ball gag</div> </div> </div> <p>A <b>gag</b> is usually an item or device designed to prevent <a href="/wiki/Interpersonal_communication" title="Interpersonal communication">speech</a>, often as a restraint device to stop the subject from calling for help and keep its wearer quiet. This is usually done by blocking the <a href="/wiki/Mouth" title="Mouth">mouth</a>, partially or completely, or attempting to prevent the <a href="/wiki/Tongue" title="Tongue">tongue</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lip" title="Lip">lips</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Jaw" title="Jaw">jaw</a> from moving in the normal patterns of speech. The more "effective" a gag appears to be, the more hazardous it is: for example, <a href="/wiki/Duct_tape" title="Duct tape">duct tape</a> is fairly effective at keeping one's mouth shut but is hazardous if for some reason (e.g., the <a href="/wiki/Common_cold" title="Common cold">common cold</a>) the subject cannot breathe freely through the nose. For this reason, a gagged person should never be left alone.</p> <p>The use of gags is commonly depicted in <a href="/wiki/Crime_fiction" title="Crime fiction">crime fiction</a> and occasionally in action films, such as <i><a href="/wiki/Raiders_of_the_Lost_Ark" title="Raiders of the Lost Ark">Raiders of the Lost Ark</a></i> and its sequel <i><a href="/wiki/Indiana_Jones_and_the_Kingdom_of_the_Crystal_Skull" title="Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull">Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull</a></i>.</p> <p>Very rarely, courts have been known to gag unruly defendants. <a href="/wiki/Bobby_Seale" title="Bobby Seale">Bobby Seale</a> is one example.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup></p> <p>During the filming of <a href="/wiki/Rope_(film)" title="Rope (film)">Rope</a>, a camera operator's foot was broken by a heavy dolly during one intensive take, and to stop his vocal noises from being recorded on the film he was gagged and hauled out of the studio so that filming could continue without interruption.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></p> <p>Occasionally a cloth over-the-mouth gag is used not to prevent speech but to keep dust and <a href="/wiki/Aerosol" title="Aerosol">aerosols</a> out of the lungs.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup></p> <p></p> <div id="toc" class="toc"> <div class="toctitle"> <h2>Contents</h2> </div> <ul> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Types_of_gags"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Types of gags</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Other_uses_of_the_word"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Other uses of the word</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="#In_symbolism"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">In symbolism</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li> <li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-5"><a href="#References"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">References</span></a></li> </ul> </div> <p></p> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Types_of_gags">Types of gags</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Types of gags">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <div class="thumb tright"> <div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"> <div id="mwe_player_0" class="PopUpMediaTransform" style="width:220px;" videopayload="&lt;div class=&quot;mediaContainer&quot; style=&quot;width:480px&quot;&gt;&lt;video id=&quot;mwe_player_1&quot; poster=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv/480px--3_Layer_Gag.ogv.jpg&quot; controls=&quot;&quot; preload=&quot;none&quot; autoplay=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:480px;height:360px&quot; class=&quot;kskin&quot; data-durationhint=&quot;56.24&quot; data-startoffset=&quot;0&quot; data-mwtitle=&quot;3_Layer_Gag.ogv&quot; data-mwprovider=&quot;wikimediacommons&quot;&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv&quot; type=&quot;video/ogg; codecs=&amp;quot;theora, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Original Ogg file, 480 × 360 (457 kbps)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;Ogg source&quot; data-width=&quot;480&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;456707&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv/3_Layer_Gag.ogv.360p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;WebM (360P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 360P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;360p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;480&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;563632&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv/3_Layer_Gag.ogv.160p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Low bandwidth WebM (160P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 160P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;160p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;214&quot; data-height=&quot;160&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;197208&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv/3_Layer_Gag.ogv.240p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small WebM (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;320&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;310328&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"><img alt="File:3 Layer Gag.ogv" style="width:220px;height:165px" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv/220px--3_Layer_Gag.ogv.jpg" /><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/53/3_Layer_Gag.ogv" title="Play media" target="new"><span class="play-btn-large"><span class="mw-tmh-playtext">Play media</span></span></a></div> <div class="thumbcaption"> <div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:3_Layer_Gag.ogv" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div> 3 Layer Gag - Stuff, Cleave, and Tape</div> </div> </div> <p>One type of gag familiar in fiction, particularly in crime <a href="/wiki/Comics" title="Comics">comics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Novels" class="mw-redirect" title="Novels">novels</a>, is a suitably sized piece of cloth pulled over the subject's mouth and tied at the back of his/her head. It is sometimes called the "detective gag" because many of its first appearances were in crime serials.</p> <p>Sometimes a gag is pushed back between the victim's front teeth into the mouth, or with a hard ball in its middle or reinforced by pushing small cloth items into the mouth. This is common <a href="/wiki/Gag_(BDSM)" title="Gag (BDSM)">in BDSM</a>, but in practice these sorts of gag can usually be got rid of by working the jaws about and/or pushing with the tongue, and they often do not stop the victim from making a loud inarticulate noise to call for help.</p> <p>Often adhesive tapes are used for improvised gags. A tape gag can cause the skin on the lips to damaged in its removal or the adhesive can cause chemical burns or reactions.</p> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Other_uses_of_the_word">Other uses of the word</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Other uses of the word">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <p>The word "gag" has come to have various extended meanings, for example:</p> <ul> <li>Various sorts of laws and orders preventing or stopping discussion or revealing of information, e.g., a parliamentary procedure to end a debate. See <a href="/wiki/Gag_order" title="Gag order">gag order</a>.</li> <li>A <a href="/wiki/Gag_rule" title="Gag rule">gag rule</a> can be a part of court proceedings and congressional proceedings.</li> <li><a href="/wiki/Gag_(medical_device)" title="Gag (medical device)">Gag (medical device)</a>, to keep the mouth open</li> <li>A <a href="/wiki/Gag_bit" title="Gag bit">gag bit</a> is a special bit type used with horses.</li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_symbolism">In symbolism</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: In symbolism">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li>Sometimes in <a href="/wiki/Political_cartoon" class="mw-redirect" title="Political cartoon">political cartoons</a>, a character is shown gagged to represent that in the real world some law or rule or order is preventing him/her from speaking about some matter (see <a href="/wiki/Gag_order" title="Gag order">gag order</a>).</li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <ul> <li><a href="/wiki/Gag_(BDSM)" title="Gag (BDSM)">Gag (BDSM)</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Muzzle_(device)" title="Muzzle (device)">Muzzle</a></li> <li><a href="/wiki/Physical_restraint" title="Physical restraint">Physical restraint</a></li> </ul> <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Gag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> <div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;"> <div class="mw-references-wrap"> <ol class="references"> <li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Lukas, J. (1969-10-30). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9A07E3D61031E73BBC4850DFB6678382679EDE">"Seale Put in Chains At Chicago 8 Trial; Judge Has Seale Chained and Gagged at Trial of the Chicago 8"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i>. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number" title="International Standard Serial Number">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/issn/0362-4331">0362-4331</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2016-03-06</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Seale+Put+in+Chains+At+Chicago+8+Trial%3B+Judge+Has+Seale+Chained+and+Gagged+at+Trial+of+the+Chicago+8&amp;rft.date=1969-10-30&amp;rft.issn=0362-4331&amp;rft.aulast=Lukas&amp;rft.aufirst=J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fquery.nytimes.com%2Fgst%2Fabstract.html%3Fres%3D9A07E3D61031E73BBC4850DFB6678382679EDE&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGag" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0040746/trivia">IMDb: <i>Rope</i></a></span></li> <li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Described, and called a "gag", in a recorded commentary in <a href="/wiki/Catalyst_(museum)" class="mw-redirect" title="Catalyst (museum)">the Catalyst chemical industry museum</a> in Runcorn (Cheshire, England), to keep alkali dust out of workers' lungs.</span></li> </ol> </div> </div>   <!--  NewPP limit report Parsed by mw1239 Cached time: